    <description><![CDATA[<div class="featured-image">
                <img src="/little-problem-in-vercellive-mode/featured-img.webp" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
            </div><h2 id="1-preface" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#1-preface" class="header-mark"></a>1 Preface</h2><p>Continuing from the previous section, after roughly completing the setup of the DoIt blog, I deployed the blog using Vercel.</p>
<p>Vercel supports a Live mode that allows website owners to make real-time modifications, and any website accessed through Vercel will automatically enter this mode.</p>
<h2 id="2-problems-encountered" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#2-problems-encountered" class="header-mark"></a>2 Problems Encountered</h2><figure><figcaption>
      <h4>Some JS files failed to load</h4>
    </figcaption>
</figure>

<p>As shown in the image, the animation for loading the blog title on the left and the opening of the search bar on the right require loading JS files, but neither of these components loaded successfully.</p>]]></description>
